<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6543a90-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s2105"><num value="2105">§ 2105.</num><heading> Report</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall provide for the investigation of the operation of this subtitle and of all laws related to marine safety, and shall require that a report be made to the Secretary annually about those matters that may require improvement or amendment.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6543a91-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/506">97 Stat. 506</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
